<paragraph id="8B84C87CFFACFFC75CB19A6BFA2BF89E" blockId="27.[151,1437,1208,2007]" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">
<emphasis id="B94F146EFFACFFC75CB19A6BFEABFAED" bold="true" box="[199,267,1281,1307]" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Adult</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="1300D4F9FFACFFC75D6A9A68FE71FAEA" box="[284,465,1282,1308]" captionStart="FIGURE 20" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1612,1636]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,287,1573]" captionTargetId="figure-62@28.[151,1436,273,1588]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 20. Merocrates ojejyella (Viette, 1986), comb. nov.: A, holotype; B, labels; C, female genitalia (posterior region), prep. P. Viette no. 5705; D, ditto, bursa copulatrix; E, abdomen. Scale bar: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406500" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406500/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Figs. 20A, B, E</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="1300D4F9FFACFFC75DA89A68FE59FAEA" box="[478,505,1282,1308]" captionStart="FIGURE 21" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1980,2004]" captionTargetBox="[164,1428,538,1938]" captionTargetId="figure-190@29.[151,1436,525,1956]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 21. Merocrates ojejyella (Viette, 1986), comb. nov.: A, head, dorsal view; B, head, lateral view; C, ventral surface of left wings; D, frenulum at base of hind wing; E, venation of forewing; F, venation of hind wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406502" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406502/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">21</figureCitation>
A–F). Wingspan, 
<quantity id="4CC36599FFACFFC75EB29A68FCB7FAEA" box="[708,791,1282,1308]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" unit="mm" value="21.0">21 mm</quantity>
. Head vestiture dark bronze; scales of the vertex narrow, anteriorly directed (
<figureCitation id="1300D4F9FFACFFC75D0C9A4CFE45FAB7" box="[378,485,1318,1345]" captionStart="FIGURE 21" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1980,2004]" captionTargetBox="[164,1428,538,1938]" captionTargetId="figure-190@29.[151,1436,525,1956]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 21. Merocrates ojejyella (Viette, 1986), comb. nov.: A, head, dorsal view; B, head, lateral view; C, ventral surface of left wings; D, frenulum at base of hind wing; E, venation of forewing; F, venation of hind wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406502" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406502/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Fig. 21A</figureCitation>
). Antenna dark brown with light brown annulets; scape whitish, orange and black, without pecten. Labial palpus very large, sickle-shaped, yellowish grey, with the outer suface of segment 2 dark brown proximally (
<figureCitation id="1300D4F9FFACFFC75D049A1AFE7AFA7C" box="[370,474,1392,1418]" captionStart="FIGURE 21" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1980,2004]" captionTargetBox="[164,1428,538,1938]" captionTargetId="figure-190@29.[151,1436,525,1956]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 21. Merocrates ojejyella (Viette, 1986), comb. nov.: A, head, dorsal view; B, head, lateral view; C, ventral surface of left wings; D, frenulum at base of hind wing; E, venation of forewing; F, venation of hind wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406502" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406502/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Fig. 21B</figureCitation>
). Body dark bronze dorsally (abdomen almost black), yellowish grey ventrally. Legs yellowish grey, outwards with dark brown areas (distally on femora; proximally on tibiae); tibial spurs dark brown on outer surface. Dorsal surface of forewing dark purplish brown with many yellowish, transverse short strigae (more numerous along costa), which tend to form longer lines below the middle and the extremity of the upper edge of the discal cell; fringe yellowish. Hind wing blackish grey, with its outer margin concave at the extremity of M 
<subScript id="17BFCA39FFACFFC759FA997CFA34F9D2" attach="left" box="[1420,1428,1558,1572]" fontSize="6" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">1</subScript>
; fringe greyish. Ventral surface of forewing dark brown, though yellowish along costa and inner margin. Ventral surface of hind wing dark brown; costa yellowish. Forewing venation (
<figureCitation id="1300D4F9FFACFFC75FC99927FBF2F991" box="[959,1106,1613,1639]" captionStart="FIGURE 21" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1980,2004]" captionTargetBox="[164,1428,538,1938]" captionTargetId="figure-190@29.[151,1436,525,1956]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 21. Merocrates ojejyella (Viette, 1986), comb. nov.: A, head, dorsal view; B, head, lateral view; C, ventral surface of left wings; D, frenulum at base of hind wing; E, venation of forewing; F, venation of hind wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406502" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406502/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Figs. 21C, E</figureCitation>
): 
<collectionCode id="ED2A50B9FFACFFC7581E9927FBDBF991" box="[1128,1147,1613,1639]" country="Chile" name="Departamento de Geologia, Universidad de Chile" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">R</collectionCode>
<subScript id="17BFCA39FFACFFC7580C9935FB22F99B" attach="left" box="[1146,1154,1631,1645]" fontSize="6" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">4</subScript>
and 
<collectionCode id="ED2A50B9FFACFFC758CA9927FB6FF991" box="[1212,1231,1613,1639]" country="Chile" name="Departamento de Geologia, Universidad de Chile" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">R</collectionCode>
<subScript id="17BFCA39FFACFFC758B89935FB76F99B" attach="left" box="[1230,1238,1631,1645]" fontSize="6" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">5</subScript>
merged together, forming a single vein that runs to the apex; base of 
<collectionCode id="ED2A50B9FFACFFC75EAD9918FD4EF97A" box="[731,750,1650,1676]" country="Chile" name="Departamento de Geologia, Universidad de Chile" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">R</collectionCode>
<subScript id="17BFCA39FFACFFC75E9899EEFD56F964" attach="left" box="[750,758,1668,1682]" fontSize="6" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">2</subScript>
remote from 
<collectionCode id="ED2A50B9FFACFFC75FE79918FC04F97A" box="[913,932,1650,1676]" country="Chile" name="Departamento de Geologia, Universidad de Chile" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">R</collectionCode>
<subScript id="17BFCA39FFACFFC75FD599EEFC0BF964" attach="left" box="[931,939,1668,1682]" fontSize="6" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">1</subScript>
and separate from 
<collectionCode id="ED2A50B9FFACFFC758F29918FB37F97A" box="[1156,1175,1650,1676]" country="Chile" name="Departamento de Geologia, Universidad de Chile" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">R</collectionCode>
<subScript id="17BFCA39FFACFFC758E199EEFB3FF964" attach="left" box="[1175,1183,1668,1682]" fontSize="6" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">3</subScript>
, which is stalked with 
<collectionCode id="ED2A50B9FFACFFC75CE199FDFF0AF947" box="[151,170,1687,1713]" country="Chile" name="Departamento de Geologia, Universidad de Chile" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">R</collectionCode>
<subScript id="17BFCA39FFACFFC75CDC99C3FF64F941" attach="left" box="[170,196,1705,1719]" fontSize="6" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">4+5</subScript>
; M 
<subScript id="17BFCA39FFACFFC75C9C99C3FF52F941" attach="left" box="[234,242,1705,1719]" fontSize="6" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">2</subScript>
arising closer to M 
<subScript id="17BFCA39FFACFFC75DBE99C3FE70F941" attach="left" box="[456,464,1705,1719]" fontSize="6" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">3</subScript>
than to M 
<subScript id="17BFCA39FFACFFC75E3699C3FDE8F941" attach="left" box="[576,584,1705,1719]" fontSize="6" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">1</subScript>
; CuA 
<subScript id="17BFCA39FFACFFC75EFD99C3FD33F941" attach="left" box="[651,659,1705,1719]" fontSize="6" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">1</subScript>
free, arising closer to CuA 
<subScript id="17BFCA39FFACFFC75FCB99C3FC65F941" attach="left" box="[957,965,1705,1719]" fontSize="6" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">2</subScript>
than to M 
<subScript id="17BFCA39FFACFFC7584099C3FB9EF941" attach="left" box="[1078,1086,1705,1719]" fontSize="6" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">3</subScript>
; CuA 
<subScript id="17BFCA39FFACFFC758F799C3FB29F941" attach="left" box="[1153,1161,1705,1719]" fontSize="6" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">2</subScript>
strongly arched, coming very close to the distal section of CuP (
<figureCitation id="1300D4F9FFACFFC75E3A99D1FD12F923" box="[588,690,1723,1749]" captionStart="FIGURE 21" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1980,2004]" captionTargetBox="[164,1428,538,1938]" captionTargetId="figure-190@29.[151,1436,525,1956]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 21. Merocrates ojejyella (Viette, 1986), comb. nov.: A, head, dorsal view; B, head, lateral view; C, ventral surface of left wings; D, frenulum at base of hind wing; E, venation of forewing; F, venation of hind wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406502" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406502/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Fig. 21E</figureCitation>
). Frenulum composed of four bristles (
<figureCitation id="1300D4F9FFACFFC7581399D1FB6DF923" box="[1125,1229,1723,1749]" captionStart="FIGURE 21" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1980,2004]" captionTargetBox="[164,1428,538,1938]" captionTargetId="figure-190@29.[151,1436,525,1956]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 21. Merocrates ojejyella (Viette, 1986), comb. nov.: A, head, dorsal view; B, head, lateral view; C, ventral surface of left wings; D, frenulum at base of hind wing; E, venation of forewing; F, venation of hind wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406502" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406502/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Fig. 21D</figureCitation>
). Hind wing venation (
<figureCitation id="1300D4F9FFACFFC75CA7998AFE94F90C" box="[209,308,1760,1786]" captionStart="FIGURE 21" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1980,2004]" captionTargetBox="[164,1428,538,1938]" captionTargetId="figure-190@29.[151,1436,525,1956]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 21. Merocrates ojejyella (Viette, 1986), comb. nov.: A, head, dorsal view; B, head, lateral view; C, ventral surface of left wings; D, frenulum at base of hind wing; E, venation of forewing; F, venation of hind wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406502" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406502/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Fig. 21F</figureCitation>
): subcosta long, diverging from the upper edge of the cell from approximately the middle of the latter; Rs free, running to apex; Rs and M 
<subScript id="17BFCA39FFACFFC75E55987DFD8BF8D3" attach="left" box="[547,555,1815,1829]" fontSize="6" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">1</subScript>
separate, diverging distad; M 
<subScript id="17BFCA39FFACFFC75F0C987DFC22F8D3" attach="left" box="[890,898,1815,1829]" fontSize="6" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">2</subScript>
arched, arising closer to M 
<subScript id="17BFCA39FFACFFC758C1987DFB1FF8D3" attach="left" box="[1207,1215,1815,1829]" fontSize="6" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">3</subScript>
than to M 
<subScript id="17BFCA39FFACFFC75942987DFA9CF8D3" attach="left" box="[1332,1340,1815,1829]" fontSize="6" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">1</subScript>
: M 
<subScript id="17BFCA39FFACFFC75912987DFACCF8D3" attach="left" box="[1380,1388,1815,1829]" fontSize="6" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">3</subScript>
and CuA 
<subScript id="17BFCA39FFACFFC75CBA9856FF74F8BC" attach="left" box="[204,212,1852,1866]" fontSize="6" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">1</subScript>
connate; CuA 
<subScript id="17BFCA39FFACFFC75D0F9856FE21F8BC" attach="left" box="[377,385,1852,1866]" fontSize="6" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">1</subScript>
and CuA 
<subScript id="17BFCA39FFACFFC75D869856FE58F8BC" attach="left" box="[496,504,1852,1866]" fontSize="6" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">2</subScript>
fairly remote proximally. Abdominal segments (
<figureCitation id="1300D4F9FFACFFC758529840FB29F8B2" box="[1060,1161,1834,1860]" captionStart="FIGURE 20" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1612,1636]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,287,1573]" captionTargetId="figure-62@28.[151,1436,273,1588]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 20. Merocrates ojejyella (Viette, 1986), comb. nov.: A, holotype; B, labels; C, female genitalia (posterior region), prep. P. Viette no. 5705; D, ditto, bursa copulatrix; E, abdomen. Scale bar: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406500" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406500/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Fig. 20E</figureCitation>
) without spinose zones; antero-abdominal sternum with short apodemes (that widen caudad) and weakly pigmented, rather short venulae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B84C87CFFACFFC05CB19819FAAAFF23" blockId="27.[151,1437,1208,2007]" lastBlockId="28.[151,1436,151,250]" lastPageId="28" lastPageNumber="179" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">
<emphasis id="B94F146EFFACFFC75CB19819FE26F87B" box="[199,390,1907,1933]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Female genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="1300D4F9FFACFFC75DE29819FD87F878" box="[404,551,1907,1934]" captionStart="FIGURE 20" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1612,1636]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,287,1573]" captionTargetId="figure-62@28.[151,1436,273,1588]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 20. Merocrates ojejyella (Viette, 1986), comb. nov.: A, holotype; B, labels; C, female genitalia (posterior region), prep. P. Viette no. 5705; D, ditto, bursa copulatrix; E, abdomen. Scale bar: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406500" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406500/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Figs. 20C, D</figureCitation>
): See also the line drawing given by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAAB58DFFACFFC75FC89819FBECF87B" author="Viette, P. E. L." box="[958,1100,1907,1933]" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" pagination="109 - 118" refId="ref24658" refString="Viette, P. E. L. (1986) Nouveaux Microlepidopteres de Madagascar (Oecophoridae et Gelechiidae) (New species of Malagasy Microlepidoptera-Oecophoridae and Gelechiidae). Bulletin mensuel de la Societe linneenne de Lyon, 55 (4), 109 - 118. https: // doi. org / 10.3406 / linly. 1986.10753" type="journal article" year="1986">Viette (1986</bibRefCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="1300D4F9FFACFFC758209819FB08F87B" box="[1110,1192,1907,1933]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="18.[151,250,1735,1759]" captionTargetBox="[151,1415,750,1712]" captionTargetId="figure-160@18.[151,1436,736,1712]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 13. Torodora cameronella (Viette, [1957]), comb. nov.: A, holotype; B, labels; C, male genitalia, prep. P. Viette no. 2761; D, aedeagus; E abdomen. Scale bar for the genitalia and aedeagus: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406486" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406486/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
). Corpus bursae elongate, not clearly delimited anteriorly. Ductus bursae as a mere extension of the corpus, distinctly swollen around the insertion of the ductus seminalis. Antrum present, rather small, tapering anteriorly. Ostium bursae in the membranous anteroventral region of segment 
<collectionCode id="ED2A50B9FFABFFC05E4F9FFDFDCDFF47" box="[569,621,151,177]" pageId="28" pageNumber="179">VIII</collectionCode>
. Apophyses anteriores tubular, though rather short; apophyses posteriores a bit more than twice as long as the former. Papillae anales separate, posteriorly acute in ventral view.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
